Investment and Business Support Team






David Paradice - President USA Operations B.Comm, ACA, ASIA, FAICD DIP  
David has 30 years' experience in equity investments. Prior to establishing Paradice Investment Management in 1999 David spent five years as the smaller companies fund manager at Mercantile Mutual specialising in small company research/funds management. Prior to joining Mercantile Mutual, he held the position of small listed and unlisted portfolio manager with the NSW State Superannuation Investment and Management Corporation. David is currently based in Denver where he is overseeing growth opportunities for Paradice Investment Management LLC.



 
 


 
Peter Manley - Chief Operating Officer BComm, Grad Dip-Applied Finance & Investments  Peter joined Paradice in 2015 and assumed the position of COO in May 2016. Peter has over 21 years of experience in the funds management industry having previously spent 16 years at GMO Australia Limited as the Asia-Pacific COO and CFO and prior to that having worked in NM Rothschild & Sons Limited, Macquarie Investment Management Limited and Banker Trust Limited. Peter is a member of Chartered Accountants Ireland, has a B.Comm from University College Dublin and a Graduate Diploma in Applied Finance and Investments from the Securities Institute of Australia.



 



 
Lucinda Hill - Chief Operating Officer US Office BA  Lucinda joined the Global Equities Team in Denver in 2014. Prior to this Lucinda held the role of Client Services Manager in the Paradice Sydney office where she was responsible for all client and consultant relationships as well as compliance and various operational functions. Before joining Paradice in 2010 Lucinda held Client Services roles at boutique fund managers in Sydney, London & Geneva.  Lucinda has over 11 years of experience in the investment management industry. 



 




 





Jude Fernandez – National Sales Manager

Jude joined Paradice as National Sales Manager in 2015. Prior to joining Paradice Jude spent over 9 years at Schroders where since 2006 he was a National Account Manager within the distribution team responsible for managing and driving the national strategy for key dealer group relationships. Prior to that Jude also worked at State Street in various roles within its corporate actions, account management, unit pricing and business consulting areas.



 
 



Dario Conte - Key Account Manager  Dario joined Paradice as a Key Account Manager in 2016. Dario has 11 years of experience in the financial services industry and joins Paradice from RARE Infrastructure where he was a Senior Business Development Manager responsible for NSW & QLD. Prior to this Dario held various roles across investment management and wealth management for companies including Fidante Partners (Challenger), Asgard Wealth Solutions and Octopus Investments & Santander Private Bank in London.



 




 




 




 


























